      "message": "Line 358: 🟡 Suggestion: The congestion callback fires every RTCP cycle while loss stays above 3%, even if the video side has already throttled and is in cooldown. This can create repeated cross-stream work/log spam for persistent loss and makes multiple video streams each apply their own cooldown independently. Add audio-side hysteresis/cooldown or only notify on threshold crossing so one sustained congestion episode maps to one reduction request.\n\n```suggestion\nif (pondLoss \u003e\u003d AUDIO_CONGESTION_THRESHOLD \u0026\u0026 lastAudioCongestionSignal_ + AUDIO_CONGESTION_COOLDOWN \u003c\u003d clock::now()) {\n    lastAudioCongestionSignal_ \u003d clock::now();\n    // copy and invoke callback\n}\n```",
