      "message": "[Critical] Line 52: 🔴 Critical Issues: `shouldSend()` blocks the media send path to simulate jitter. On RTP sender threads this can back up encoding/pacing, distort timestamps, and make tests exercise local thread stalls rather than network jitter. Model jitter with queued delayed delivery, or keep this class packet-drop/bandwidth-only and remove blocking jitter from the synchronous socket write path.\n\n```suggestion\n// Do not sleep in SocketPair::writeCallback(); either enqueue delayed packets on a worker\n// or expose jitter only in tests that explicitly call the simulator outside media send paths.\n```",
