      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 632: 🔴 Critical Issues: The simulator is applied only to non-RTCP packets, but `writeCallback` carries both RTP and RTCP packets from SRTP/DTLS paths. Silently returning `buf_size` for a dropped RTP packet means the upper layer records the packet as sent, but the simulator\u0027s bandwidth accounting excludes RTCP and control overhead, so QoS tests will overestimate available media bandwidth and under-report congestion. Either account for RTCP bytes while never dropping them, or document/rename the simulator as RTP-only and adjust tests accordingly.\n\n```suggestion\nif (sim) {\n    if (isRTCP) {\n        sim-\u003eaccountControlPacket(static_cast\u003csize_t\u003e(buf_size));\n    } else if (!sim-\u003eshouldSend(static_cast\u003csize_t\u003e(buf_size))) {\n        return buf_size;\n    }\n}\n```",
