      "message": "Line 231: 🟡 Suggestion: The audio congestion callback captures the whole `SIPCall` and scans current sessions on the RTCP checker thread. This couples media adaptation to SIP call internals and makes lock ordering harder to reason about. Prefer wiring audio/video sessions together at media-session configuration time with weak video-session references, so the callback only targets the paired video RTP sessions and does not need to re-enter call session enumeration.\n\n```suggestion\naudioRtp-\u003esetCongestionCallback([videoWeak \u003d std::weak_ptr(videoRtp)](float audioLoss) {\n    if (auto video \u003d videoWeak.lock())\n        video-\u003eonAudioCongestion(audioLoss);\n});\n```",
